# Content Marketing Suite - Cursor AI Rules
# These rules guide Cursor's AI Composer when editing this project

## Project Context
You are helping develop an AI-powered content marketing suite.
- Runtime: Python 3.12 via UV package manager
- Web UI: Streamlit dashboard
- AI APIs: Groq (llama-3.3-70b-versatile) + Google Gemini (gemini-1.5-flash)
- All APIs must be FREE tier only — never suggest paid APIs

## Code Style Rules
1. Every Python file starts with the UV + Cursor compatibility header:
   ```python
   # Cursor-compatible + UV-ready
   # Run: uv run python <filename>.py
   ```
2. Use `from dotenv import load_dotenv; load_dotenv()` at module level
3. All CLI entry points need `if __name__ == "__main__":` guards
4. Error messages must be prefixed with `[UV]` for CLI or `[ERROR]` for Streamlit
5. Use type hints for all function signatures
6. Docstrings required for all public functions (Google style)

## Architecture Rules
- agents/ = AI logic (researcher, writer, SEO, social formatter)
- utils/ = Pure utility functions (no AI calls)
- app.py = Streamlit UI only (thin layer over agents/)
- cli.py = Argparse CLI (thin layer over agents/)
- Never put business logic directly in app.py or cli.py

## API Usage Rules
- Groq: Use for fast generation (llama-3.3-70b-versatile model)
- Gemini: Use for research/analysis (gemini-1.5-flash model)
- Always handle API rate limits with exponential backoff
- Always check for env var existence before making API calls
- Mock API calls in tests (never hit real APIs in tests)

## Streamlit Rules
- Use st.session_state for all persistent state
- Tabs: Generate | SEO Analysis | Content Calendar | Settings
- Show spinner during API calls
- Download buttons for all generated content
- Never use st.experimental_ functions (deprecated)

## When Adding New Features
1. Add utility functions to utils/
2. Add AI agents to agents/
3. Wire into both app.py (Streamlit tab) and cli.py (argparse subcommand)
4. Add tests to tests/
5. Update README.md with new usage examples

## Dependency Management
- Add new deps to pyproject.toml [project.dependencies]
- Run `uv sync` after adding dependencies
- Never use pip install directly
- Pin major versions but allow minor updates: "package>=X.Y.0"
